:DirectionChoice:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/perfmeter.handbook
Direction:

Dials or strip charts can be displayed either 
horizontally or vertically. 

Choose horizontal or vertical.

:DisplayChoice:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/perfmeter.handbook
Display:

You can display either speedometer dials or strip 
graphs to show the statistics.

Choose dial or graph.

:GraphChoice:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/perfmeter.handbook
Graph type:

Strip graphs can be either simple line graphs or
solidly filled. 

Choose line or solid.

:SaveSamples:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/perfmeter.handbook
Log Samples:

Choose if you want to save statistic samples.

In the Filename field, you can name the file where
samples are to be saved.

WARNING: Do not leave Performance Meter running
for a long time with Log Samples turned on--the
file where samples are saved will increase in
size until your system runs out of disk space.

:SampleName:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/perfmeter.handbook
Filename:

Enter the name of the file where statistic
samples are to be saved.

If you do not specify a file name, Performance
Meter will create a file in your home directory. 

